BRITAIN’S PRIME MINISTER is making a risky move by calling for a general election in December. Will it succeed any more than it did for his predecessor? In Japan, both the government and the people take a dim view of soft-drug use; we ask why. And tourists make a dangerous and defiant last-minute dash up Uluru, Australia’s most famous rock. Runtime: 22 min For full access to print, digital and audio editions of The Economist, subscribe here: www.economist.com/radiooffer    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn